description: Gets information about environment members for an Cloud9 development environment.

parameters.name: permissions
parameters.description: The type of environment member permissions to get information about. Available values include: owner: Owns the environment. read-only: Has read-only access to the environment. read-write: Has read-write access to the environment. If no value is specified, information about all environment members are returned. (string) ---

nested_items.name: memberships
nested_items.description: Information about the environment members for the environment.

nested_items.name: permissions
nested_items.description: The type of environment member permissions associated with this environment member. Available values include:
read-only: Has read-only access to the environment.
read-write: Has read-write access to the environment.

nested_items.name: userId
nested_items.description: The user ID in Identity and Access Management (IAM) of the environment member.

nested_items.name: userArn
nested_items.description: The Amazon Resource Name (ARN) of the environment member.

nested_items.name: environmentId
nested_items.description: The ID of the environment for the environment member.

nested_items.name: lastAccess
nested_items.description: The time, expressed in epoch time format, when the environment member last opened the environment.

nested_items.name: nextToken
nested_items.description: If there are more than 25 items in the list, only the first 25 items are returned, along with a unique string called a next token. To get the next batch of items in the list, call this operation again, adding the next token to the call.
